---
name: agent-mcp-server
version: 0.1.0
description: Expose an app's std.agent tools over MCP with serveAgentToolsMcp, so an external agent can drive them.
---

# Agent tools over MCP

Declare tools once as `std.agent` `AgentTool`s (the same ones an in-process agent loop
would use), then expose them over MCP with a single call — an external agent (Claude
Code, another rozum agent, …) can now drive the same tools.

[agentTool, toolOk, toolError, objectSchema](std/agent.ssc)
[serveAgentToolsMcp](std/agent-mcp.ssc)
[Transport](std/mcp/server.ssc)
[jsonValue](std/json.ssc)

```scalascript
val tools = List(
  agentTool("greet", "Greet a person by name",
            objectSchema("\"name\":{\"type\":\"string\"}", List("name"))) { argsJson =>
    val name = jsonValue(argsJson).get("name").asString
    if name == "" then toolError("name is required")
    else toolOk("{\"text\":\"Hello, " + name + "!\"}")
  }
)

println("agent tools exposed over MCP (stdio)")
serveAgentToolsMcp(tools, Transport.Stdio)
```
